unregister setting "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
==================================================================

NAME
----

unregister setting - Allows clean de-registration of registered settings. Should be used

SYNOPSIS
--------

Allows clean de-registration of registered settings. Should be used
mostly in [deactivation
hooks](/Function_Reference/register_deactivation_hook "Function Reference/register deactivation hook").

USAGE
-----

` <?php unregister_setting( $option_group, $option_name, $sanitize_callback ); ?> `

PARAMETERS
----------

 `$option_group` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Group the option belongs to (used in
    register\_setting).
    Default: *None*

 `$option_name` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Name of the option
    Default: *None*

 `$sanitize_callback` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Function that fills the section with the desired
    content. The function should echo its output.
    Default: *None*

RETURN VALUES
-------------

 (void) 
:   This function does not return a value.

CHANGE LOG
----------

Since: [2.7.0](/Version_2.7 "Version 2.7")

SOURCE FILE
-----------

`unregister_setting()` is located in `wp-admin/includes/plugin.php`.

